 Kogi State Governor, Yahaya Bello. Photo/KINGLEYFANWO  This was contained in a statement signed yesterday by the NUJ Chairman, Adeiza Momohjimoh, and Secretary, Ademu Seidu, and made available to newsmen in Lokoja. The statement described the death of the octogenarian as shocking and painful. NUJ urged the governor’s aide to take solace in the fact that his father lived an impactful life as exemplified in the quality of children he left behind. “Kindly convey our deepest condolences to your immediate family, friends and good people of Kogi on this painful incident,” it noted. “We pray Allah to grant his soul eternal rest and the family the fortitude to bear this irreparable loss,” the statement added. To enable commenting and other interactive features, please switch to the more advanced .